In England, in the seven days to 05 November, there were 201,367 new confirmed cases (356.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 October, there were 235,437 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 14% (34,070 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 10 November is 7,984,769 (14,119.8 cases per 100,000 population).
